# === KERNEL SAFETY & DETERMINISM RULES (HARD) ===

- This repository contains kernel-level code.
- Do NOT invent or redesign system behavior.
- Do NOT introduce heuristics, randomness, or arrival-time ordering.
- Determinism is a hard requirement, not a preference.

- Arbitration logic MUST be explicit, deterministic, and auditable.
- Winner selection rules MUST be written exactly as specified.
- Never silently "improve" throughput or availability.
- Safety and correctness always override performance.

- Do NOT refactor unrelated code when modifying kernel logic.
- Minimal diff is mandatory for kernel changes.

- If constraints conflict or cannot be satisfied:
  STOP and explain the blocking reason instead of guessing.

- No new code may directly modify ResourceLock / TimeSlot reservation state.
- All future changes MUST go through kernel syscalls or events.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Section D: CURSOR PATCH GOVERNANCE LAYER
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Rule 16: SINGLE-FILE PATCH MODE (DEFAULT)

Cursor is restricted to SINGLE-FILE PATCH MODE unless explicitly elevated.

- Cursor may only modify exactly ONE file per operation.
- Multi-file edits are forbidden by default.
- No directory-level operations allowed.
- No project-wide refactors allowed.

Elevation requires explicit MODE [EVOLUTION] authorization.


Rule 17: NO AUTO DOCUMENTATION GENERATION

Cursor is strictly prohibited from auto-generating:

- README.md
- ARCHITECTURE.md
- DESIGN.md
- ROADMAP.md
- KERNEL.md
- API.md
- SECURITY.md
- CHANGELOG.md
- Any *.md file

Unless explicitly requested via MODE [EVOLUTION] + DOC_SCOPE declaration.


Rule 18: NO PROJECT SCANNING

Cursor must not:

- Scan the entire repository
- Load multi-module context
- Analyze whole directories
- Summarize the system
- Re-interpret system architecture

Context scope MUST be limited to the target file.


Rule 19: MINIMAL DIFF MANDATE

All patches MUST:

- Be minimal
- Be local
- Avoid stylistic refactors
- Avoid code reformatting
- Avoid non-functional changes


Rule 20: NO FILE CREATION BY DEFAULT

Cursor must not create:

- New files
- New directories
- New documentation artifacts

Unless explicitly authorized by MODE [EVOLUTION].


Rule 21: TOKEN SAFETY GOVERNANCE

Cursor must operate under Token Safety Mode:

- Avoid large context ingestion
- Avoid repository-wide inference
- Avoid summarization tasks
- Avoid architectural redesign tasks

Cursor must prioritize determinism, auditability, and token containment.


Rule 22: KERNEL ZONE RESTRICTION

For any path under:

- /kernel/*
- /decision_slots/*
- /ats_signals/*
- /human_loop/*
- /signal_delivery/*

Cursor must enforce:

- Single-file patch
- No new file creation
- No markdown
- No documentation
- No refactor
- No formatting
- Minimal diff only

Violations require STOP + justification, not guessing.


Rule 23: DOC_SCOPE (Explicit Override Gate)

Documentation generation is only allowed when ALL of the following are present:

- MODE [EVOLUTION]
- DOC_SCOPE = {explicit file list}
- User explicitly authorizes documentation creation
- Scope is limited to declared files only

Otherwise, documentation generation is forbidden.


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
END OF CURSOR GOVERNANCE LAYER
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━